article.description: Robert Morris tops Bryant 66-53 to advance
article.headline: Robert Morris tops Bryant 66-53 to advance
article.linkText: Robert Morris tops Bryant 66-53 to advance
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Kavon Stewart scored 19 points, Rodney Pryor added 12, and No. 2 seed Robert Morris rallied to beat third-seeded Bryant 66-53 on Saturday to advance to the Northeast Conference tournament finals. The Colonials (18-14) will face top-seeded Saint Francis (NY), which beat fifth-seeded Saint Francis (Pa) 62-48 on Saturday. Lucky Jones scored 11 for Robert Morris, which never trailed in the first half. The Colonials opened with a 14-3 lead and Stewart scored eight straight points late in the half to produce a 30-25 halftime lead. Bryant rallied to tie it at 35 on a 3 by Dyami Starks, then led 43-40 on a jumper by Bosko Kostur. But Robert Morris ripped a 19-5 run and led 61-51 on a layup by Elijah Minnie with 3:15 left, then finished on a 7-2 run. Starks led Bryant (16-15) with 19 points, making 5 of 11 3-pointers, and Kostur added 10 points.
